  "text": "The Starlark BUILD file evaluation pipeline works as follows: PackageFunction (Skyframe) calls PackageFactory.executeBuildFile(), which sets up a StarlarkThread and invokes Eval to interpret the BUILD file. StarlarkThread (net/starlark/java/eval/) is the Starlark runtime environment. BzlLoadFunction handles loading .bzl files via Skyframe. The rule() and macro() builtin functions are implemented in StarlarkRuleClassFunctions (in analysis/starlark/), which creates StarlarkRuleFunction and MacroClass objects respectively. RuleClass defines rule schemas, RuleFactory instantiates rules, and MacroClass/MacroInstance handle first-class macros. StarlarkNativeModule provides the 'native' object in BUILD files. Package.Builder (inner class at line 1059 of Package.java) accumulates targets during evaluation. BzlInitThreadContext provides thread-local context during .bzl initialization.",
